The Publisher of SaharaReporters Omoyele Sowore has been released from DSS detention. The activist was released from detention on Tuesday following the directive from President Muhammadu Buhari government. The Attorney-General of the Federation and Minister of Justice, Abubakar Malami (SAN), had on Tuesday ordered his freedom. More to come… Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.